&quot;PLEASE CHECK OUT HACK POST<br>
Wed Nov 19 23:31:49 US/Eastern 1997&quot; <br><br>
If you go to that thread, I have posted only part of what was deleted after the above post. <br><br>
The threads at that point seems like a nice dialog between a medic vet who has tracers in his .45 pistol and a multi person individual. But it doesn’t take much to see it all as a set up dialog, faked for the purpose of an individuals glory or to submit the site for an award? <br><br>
You are right this is Marc's site, His house, his rules, you say. but it also belongs to those who have chosen to post about their experiences. <br><br>
These threads have some very interesting conversations posted already that do not need to be glorified in order to obtain some type of recognition. <br><br>
I have no problem with a good dialog among vets and protestors when they are honest about their involvement and convictions. Deceitfulness as to being something you're not in order to deceive veterans suffering from PTSD is mean spirited sick and something I could not tolerate. Is that why we were invited here for? To be used? Abused and set up? That’s what it seems like to me. But then again. <br>
I’m not sorry, but that is my opinion.<br>

